T1  - Management Economics in a Large Retail Company
AU  - Siebert, W. Stanley
AU  - Zubanov, Nikolay
Y1  - 2010/07/02
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1100.1188
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1100.1188
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1398
EP  - 1414
VL  - 56
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We use unique data from 245 stores of a UK retailer to study links among middle (store) manager skills, sales, and manager pay. We find that, of the six management practice areas surveyed, the most important is ?commercial awareness,? where abler managers achieve up to 13.9% higher sales per worker. We find that many stores have poor managers on this indicator. However, the company is careful to incentivize managers, operating a scheme giving shares (approximately 20%) in both positive and negative deviations of actual sales from expected. Abler managers do not receive higher pay, implying that their skills are company specific.
